# Pad Thai with Shrimp

> A refined take on a Thai classic. #thai #noodles #fancy

- Thai Rice Stick Noodles | 8 oz | 

## Sauce

- Tamarind Concentrate | 1/4 cup | 
- Premium Fish Sauce | 1/4 cup | 
- Palm Sugar | 1/3 cup | 
- Chili Powder | 1-2 tsp | 

## Proteins & Main Ingredients

- Vegetable Oil Or Rendered Pork Fat | 3 tbsp | 
- Garlic | 4 cloves | 
- Large Shrimp | 10-12 | 
- Pressed tofu | 1/4 cup | Thinly sliced
- Eggs | 2 | 
- Dried Shrimp | 2 tbsp | 
- Salted Radish | 1 tbsp | 

## Vegetables & Garnish

- Bean Sprouts | 2 cups + extra for garnish | 
- Chinese Chives Or Green Onions | 5 stalks | 
- Roasted Unsalted Peanuts | 1/4 cup | 
- Lime | 1 | 
- Red Pepper Flakes |  | 

## Cooking

1. Prepare the sauce in a small saucepan, warm ingredients over low heat until palm sugar is dissolved.

2. In a large pan or wok, heat oil or pork fat, sautÃ© garlic, add shrimp, tofu, dried shrimp, and radish.

3. Add eggs, then noodles and sauce. Stir vigorously.

4. Once noodles are done, toss in bean sprouts and chives.

5. Serve with garnishes.

> Note: Adjust ingredients based on preference and servings.
